      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Chicago has plenty of upscale spots for solo visitors. The Gold Coast and Lincoln Park areas are generally safe and upscale, with plenty of high-end restaurants and shops. You can visit the Art Institute of Chicago, take a stroll along the Magnificent Mile, or enjoy a drink at a rooftop bar in the River North area. As for areas to avoid, steer clear of Englewood and West Garfield Park, as they have higher crime rates and are not typically considered safe for tourists. Also, be cautious of some areas in South Side neighborhoods like Roseland and Hegewisch, which have higher crime rates and are generally less tourist-friendly.",
