      "content": "i get that, but even looking at the vibe, it feels like people usually equate \"safe\" with being in places that are mostly white, even if the crime rates aren't actually that much different in other spots. do you think there's a tendency for people to label neighborhoods with more diverse or minority populations as \"dangerous\" just because of the way they look or act compared to the more traditional \"upscale\" areas?",
